Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/thresholdAttainmentAt
Object: Date time at which a threshold is met.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/hasGovernmentResponse
Object: Relates a petition to a Government response.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/fromPlace
Object: Relates a located signature count to the place the signatures came from.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/hasDebate
Object: Relates a petition to a debate.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/Rejection
Object: Explicit moderation option for when a petition is rejected.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/Place
Object: A place. Any kind of place.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/LocatedSignatureCount
Object: The number of signatures on a petition from a given place.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/
Object: Petition ontology for UK Parliament. Covers the public surface area of petitions.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/hasCreator
Object: Relates a petition to the person who created it.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/rejectionCode
Object: A number identifying a specific rejection code.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/closedAt
Object: Date time at which the petition was closed.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/hasLocatedSignatureCount
Object: Relates a petition to a located signature count.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/hasThresholdAttainment
Object: Relates a petition to a threshold attainment.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/ModerationOption
Object: The available moderation options for a petition. Might be awaiting moderation, rejected and unpublished, rejected and published or accepted and published.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/signatureCountRetrievedAt
Object: Date time at which a located signature count was retrieved from the petitions API.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/action
Object: The action text (title) of the petition entered by the petition creator.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/rejectionDetails
Object: Written explanation of why a petition was rejected.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/background
Object: A background explanation of why the petition was created entered by the petition creator.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/thresholdSignatureNumber
Object: The number of signatures required to meet a threshold.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/Threshold
Object: A type of threshold. Might be moderation threshold, government response threshold or debate threshold.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/Moderation
Object: The moderation state of a petition. Might be awaiting moderation, rejected and unpublished, rejected and published or accepted and published.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/Approval
Object: Explicit moderation option for when a petition is approved.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/ThresholdAttainment
Object: The threshold attainment levels a petition might pass through from moderation threshold to government response threshold to debate threshold.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/hasModerationOption
Object: Relates a moderation to its moderation option.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/hasModeration
Object: Relates a petition to its moderation states.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/signatureCount
Object: Number of signatures on a located signature count.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/additionalDetails
Object: Additional text to justify the petition entered by the petition creator.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/petition/hasThreshold
Object: Relates a threshold attainment to a threshold.
